Jesper Parnevik, signing an autograph for a young fan, is four shots back after a par 72. He is at 2-under 142. Photo: Photos By Tom Reel /San Antonio Express-News Dapper Parnevik moving up San Antonio Championship leaderboard 1 / 1 Back to Gallery His rookie season on the Champions Tour has been mostly forgettable, with just two top 10 finishes in 14 events.
But Jesper Parnevik remains one of golf’s most intriguing characters.
Nicknamed “Spaceman” for eating volcanic dust as a dietary supplement, the lanky Swede is best known for his eccentric tastes in fashion — tight-fitting disco pants, thick belts, loud colors and flipped bill hats.
Now, he’s added acting to the list, starring with his family in a reality show on Swedish TV.
After a par 72 on Saturday, Parnevik is in contention at the San Antonio Championship. His 2-under 142 total is four strokes behind co-leaders Michael Allen and Scott McCarron heading into Sunday’s final round.
